✅ 1) Introduction to Bootstrap 5

Q1 (🔥 MMI). What is Bootstrap 5 and why is it used?

✅ Answer : Bootstrap 5 is a front-end CSS framework used to build responsive, mobile-first websites quickly.
It provides ready-made grid system, UI components, utilities, and helper classes so we don’t need to write CSS from scratch.

Why Bootstrap is used?
✅ Ready-made design + layout
✅ Works on mobile + tablet + desktop
✅ No need to write too much CSS
✅ Comes with components like navbar, buttons, cards, modals, forms, etc.

Q2 (⭐ MI). What is new in Bootstrap 5 compared to Bootstrap 4?

✅ Answer:
Bootstrap 5 introduced major upgrades:

✅ No jQuery required (Bootstrap 4 depended on jQuery)
✅ Uses Vanilla JavaScript
✅ Improved grid system & utilities
✅ Added new components & utilities
✅ Better support for modern browsers

Q3 What is “mobile-first” in Bootstrap?
✅ Answer : Mobile-first means Bootstrap styles are designed for small screens first, then we add styles for bigger screens using breakpoints like sm, md, lg.

