✅ 2) Bootstrap Setup (CDN-Content Delivery Network)

Q4 (🔥 MMI). How do you add Bootstrap 5 using CDN?

✅ Answer:
To use Bootstrap 5 via CDN, we add:

✅ Bootstrap CSS in <head>
✅ Bootstrap bundle JS before closing </body>

<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

Important Point:
bootstrap.bundle.min.js includes Popper (needed for dropdown, tooltip, popover).

Q5 (⭐ MI). What is the difference between bootstrap.min.js and bootstrap.bundle.min.js?

✅ Answer:
bootstrap.min.js → Bootstrap JS only (Popper not included)
bootstrap.bundle.min.js → Bootstrap JS + Popper included
👉 So for dropdowns, tooltips, popovers → use bundle.

Q6 (✔ I). Can we use Bootstrap without JavaScript?

✅ Answer:
Yes, Bootstrap can be used without JS for layout, grid, typography, spacing, buttons, cards.
But interactive components like modal, dropdown, collapse, tooltip require JS.
