✅ 3) Grid System + Layout (MOST IMPORTANT)

Q7 (🔥 MMI). Explain Bootstrap Grid System.

✅ Answer:
Bootstrap grid system is based on 12-column layout.
It helps create responsive layouts using:
.container or .container-fluid
.row
.col-*

Example:

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-6">50%</div>
    <div class="col-6">50%</div>
  </div>
</div>

📌 Why 12 columns?
Because 12 is divisible by 2, 3, 4, 6 → easy to create equal layouts.

Key Benefits:
Responsive layout
Automatically adjusts for screen sizes
Uses Flexbox internally

Q8 (🔥 MMI). What is the difference between container and container-fluid?

✅ Answer:
✅ .container → fixed width at different breakpoints (center aligned)
✅ .container-fluid → full width 100% for all screen sizes

Example use-case:
Website page layout → .container
Full width banner/hero → .container-fluid

Q9 (⭐ MI). What is the role of row in Bootstrap?

✅ Answer:
.row is used to wrap columns and it:

Creates a horizontal group of columns
Removes extra padding using negative margins
Ensures proper alignment inside container
Without .row, columns won’t align properly.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 4) Container, Row, Column

Q10 (🔥 MMI). Explain Container → Row → Column structure.

Answer:
Bootstrap layout is built like this:

✅ Container → holds content and provides padding
✅ Row → groups columns horizontally
✅ Column → actual content area inside grid

Example:

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">Box 1</div>
    <div class="col">Box 2</div>
  </div>
</div>

Q11 What are gutters in Bootstrap?

✅ Answer : Gutters are the spacing between columns.
	g-0 → no gap
	g-3 → medium gap
	gx-4 → horizontal gap only
	gy-2 → vertical gap only

Example:
<div class="row g-3">
 <div class="col-6 bg-light">Box 1</div>
  <div class="col-6 bg-light">Box 2</div>
</div>

