✅ 5) Responsive Breakpoints (Very asked)

Q12 (🔥 MMI). What are Bootstrap 5 breakpoints?
>>✅ A breakpoint in Bootstrap means: a specific screen width (device size) where the layout changes.

Simple Meaning
📌 When screen becomes bigger/smaller (mobile → tablet → laptop), Bootstrap changes the design using breakpoints.
So breakpoint = point where responsive design “breaks” and adjusts.

Bootstrap Breakpoints (Important) :

Breakpoint	Class Prefix	Screen Size
Extra small	col-(none)    	<576px
Small		col-sm-		≥576px
Medium		col-md-		≥768px
Large		col-lg-		≥992px
Extra large	col-xl-		≥1200px
XXL		col-xxl-	≥1400px

Q13 (⭐ MI). How do you make columns responsive using breakpoints?

✅ Answer:
Use breakpoint-specific column classes:

Example:
<div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-lg-4"></div>

Meaning:

mobile: full width
small screens: half width
large screens: one-third width
