✅ 6) Essential Components (Typography, Buttons, Cards, Forms)

Q14 (⭐ MI). How does Bootstrap handle typography?

✅ Answer:
Bootstrap provides typography classes like:

Headings (h1 to h6)
.lead for highlight text
.text-center, .text-muted
.fw-bold, .fst-italic

Example:
<p class="lead fw-bold text-center">Welcome</p>

Q15 (🔥 MMI). Explain Bootstrap button classes.

✅ Answer:
Bootstrap provides pre-styled buttons:

Example:
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
<button class="btn btn-outline-danger">Delete</button>

Types:

.btn-primary, .btn-success, .btn-warning, .btn-danger
Outline buttons: .btn-outline-*
Sizes: .btn-sm, .btn-lg

Q16 (⭐ MI). What is a Bootstrap card?

✅ Answer:
Card is a flexible content container for displaying:

images
text
buttons
titles

Q17 (🔥 MMI). How do you create a Bootstrap form?

✅ Answer:
Bootstrap forms use .form-control, .form-label, .form-select.

Example:

<label class="form-label">Email</label>
<input type="email" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter email">


For select:

<select class="form-select">
  <option>India</option>
</select>

